etworks of intermediate complexity can provide a powerful tool for elucidating potential ecosystem-wide effects of apex predators and predicting the consequences ofmanagement interventions such as predator control. Integrating trophic cascades, with their array of complex interactions, with the three- dimensional structure of ecological networks, has the potential to reveal ‘ecological architecture' that neither cap- tures on its own. Key-words:},
