3. Up to 30% of species could be removed without drastically changing the structure of the network.
4. Clusters collaspe into 5 broad functional categories which tend to mirror taxonomic groups
5. This structure may be generalizable to other ecosystems, including terrestrial ones.


This is an interesting approach that could be applied to co-occurrence networks separated by predicted interaction type.},
