@article{Thibaut2012,
annote = {Interesting paper-- they examine how the portfolio effect enforces stability in reef ecosystems in the sense that it reduces regime shifts. The portfolio effect is the idea that the average flucuation in diversity/abundance or other characteristics of a community/population will be less than the fluctuations of individual species, thus promoting stability. In this case, they show that the portfolio effect in herbivorous reef fishes maintains the abundance of fish such that microalgae cannot overgrow on coral reefs. 
They also examine whether the portfolio effect is caused by reaction diversity to environmental conditions or by compensatory dynamics. They conclude it is mostly the former. 

Compensatory dynamics are always rare in empirical studies. Most people don't seem to realize this is because of mathematical reasons, not biological ones.},
